364:
1. Serenity - the state of calmness and tranquility
2. Obdurate - unyielding or stubbornly resistant to change
3. Effervescence - lively and animated enthusiasm
4. Surreptitious - secretive, stealthy, or hidden
5. Ineffable - too great or extreme to be expressed or described in words
6. Propinquity - proximity or nearness in space or time
7. Inscrutable - impossible to understand or interpret
8. Ameliorate - to make something better or more bearable
9. Avuncular - warmly affectionate or brotherly
10. Paradox - a seemingly absurd or self-contradictory statement that is actually true
